heimdall (0.5.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New Feature: Deep System Inspection (Inspect → [i])
    - Real-time ancestry tracking (Process Tree)
    - Resource pressure analysis (CPU/Mem/RSS)
    - Connection visibility & Top Talker IP tracking
    - Security audit (Privilege, public exposure, deleted binaries)
  * New Feature: Background Service Updates
    - Periodic auto-check for services.json updates from GitHub
    - SHA256 integrity verification
    - New Settings Modal (p) for update management
  * UI/UX:
    - New status-indicator (top-right) for background updates
    - Redesigned help bar (compact mode for small terminals)
    - Color-themed Settings/Interval selection dialogs
  * Misc:
    - Added --no-update CLI flag
    - Fixed debug logging NameError during startup

 -- Serkan Sunel <serkan.sunel@gmail.com>  Sun, 15 Feb 2026 23:15:00 +0200

heimdall (0.4.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New feature: Precision Kill Tree (Action Center → [t])
    - Nuclear termination for background script loops
    - Protects interactive terminal sessions from being killed
  * New feature: Process Priority Management (Action Center → [n])
    - Interactive renice modal with real-time feedback
  * New feature: OOM Score Adjustment (Action Center → [o])
    - Control process sacrificial status during RAM exhaustion
  * Improved: Tree-aware Pause/Continue mechanism
  * Added: Internal debug logging to ~/.config/heimdall/debug.log
  * UI: New visual indicators for [PAUSED] processes
  * Fixed: /proc/stat parsing for process names with spaces

 -- Serkan Sunel <serkan.sunel@gmail.com>  Sat, 14 Feb 2026 17:40:32 +0200

heimdall (0.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New feature: Connection Limit modal (Action Center → [l])
    - View active per-IP connection limits for a port
    - Quickly enforce 5/10/25/50/100 connection limits per IP (REJECT with tcp-reset)
    - Remove existing limits with one key [x]
  * Docs: Updated README with Connection Limit details and screenshots

 -- Serkan Sunel <serkan.sunel@gmail.com>  Tue, 12 Feb 2026 20:15:00 +0200

heimdall (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New feature: Kill Connections modal (Action Center → [k])
    - Lists active ESTABLISHED connections for selected port
    - Allows terminating connections via sudo ss -K or conntrack
    - Single-key selection (1-9) with visual feedback
  * Fixed: Connection deduplication (bidirectional connections now shown once)
  * Fixed: Connections now displayed from server perspective for clarity
  * Updated documentation with Kill Connections usage and examples

